defaultIan Taylordefault: We are quite different from ESPO and YPO in the sense that we do not have a warehouse and distribution operation. 
defaultMark defaultPawseydefault:default I am pleased to hear that.
defaultIan Taylordefault: We did in the far distant past, but decided that was not really for NEPO. NEPO gets its strength because we are regionally owned. It is hard enough to get collaboration going in any public sector organisation, for a whole variety of reasons, but we are strengthened by the fact that we are owned by the region, based in the region, and conscious of our obligations to our regional supply base. That gives a strength that a solo national organisation would not be able to deliver. 
default&#xa0;
defaultQ139 default&#xa0; 
