defaultMark Robinsondefault: You could possibly have an umbrella organisation for local government procurement. It is very difficult, because there is such a wide category of different things that you procure under local government. However, there is no reason why, over a period of time, you could not develop an umbrella organisation. You could perhaps start with one category of procurement like construction, or another big one like social services, or IT or something like that, and look at harmonising everything that you need to do across the 
defaultUK
default.
